01:55:51,195 --> 01:55:51,755
[SPEAKER_12]: Councilor Kerrio.

1381
01:55:52,055 --> 01:55:52,596
[SPEAKER_10]: Thank you, Mayor President.

1382
01:55:53,336 --> 01:56:06,947
[SPEAKER_10]: Well, you know, if we keep using the upper money for revenue, I mean, for revenue replacement, doesn't that kind of change the purpose of what the upper funds is for?

1383
01:56:06,987 --> 01:56:10,930
[SPEAKER_10]: That was for more for community use, I would think.

1384
01:56:12,578 --> 01:56:17,122
[SPEAKER_04]: There is a component of it that has to be used for community, as I understand it.

1385
01:56:17,422 --> 01:56:25,288
[SPEAKER_10]: I mean, I see other cities using their upper money for a lot better things than what we're using it for.

1386
01:56:25,308 --> 01:56:33,894
[SPEAKER_10]: I mean, revenue replacement, I don't know if that was what the main intent was for, but I don't think that's the best use of it.

1387
01:56:35,012 --> 01:56:36,993
[SPEAKER_12]: Okay, well- They're different buckets, correct?

1388
01:56:37,373 --> 01:56:53,819
[SPEAKER_04]: Well, just to be clear, just because you're using revenue replacement as the justification for spending the money doesn't mean that you could use revenue replacement saying, okay, I want to totally redo a park.

1389
