[SPEAKER_04]: It's the least constrained way.

1396
01:57:31,684 --> 01:57:45,138
[SPEAKER_04]: Now, from my point of view, obviously, revenue replacement, when you're looking at the general fund budget, and you're looking at the city's budget, if you have that hole that you're forced to cover every year with revenue replacement, you want to

1397
01:57:46,410 --> 01:57:49,872
[SPEAKER_04]: make sure down the road when you don't have that option that you can cover your budget.

1398
01:57:50,193 --> 01:57:55,116
[SPEAKER_04]: And that's what we have been, that's what I've been raising alarm bells about.

1399
